# Week 9 - Day 2  
## ğŸ§  LeetCode 42 - Trapping Rain Water

## ğŸ“Œ Problem Statement

Given n non-negative integers representing an elevation map where the width of each bar is 1, compute how much water it can trap after raining.

---

# ğŸ’¡ Approach 1: Prefix & Suffix Maximum (Dynamic Programming)

## ğŸ” Core Idea

At any index `i`, water trapped is:

water[i] = min(leftMax[i], rightMax[i]) - height[i]

Because:
- Water is limited by the shorter boundary.
- We need maximum height on left and right side.

---

## ğŸ§  Step-by-Step Explanation

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Create Two Arrays

- `lmax[i]` â†’ Maximum height from index 0 to i
- `rmax[i]` â†’ Maximum height from index n-1 to i

---
```cpp
  class Solution {
public:
    int trap(vector<int>& height) {
        int n = height.size();
        vector<int> lmax(n,0);
        vector<int> rmax(n,0);
        lmax[0] = height[0];
        rmax[n-1] = height[n-1];
        int ans=0;
        // left maximum
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            lmax[i] = max(lmax[i-1],height[i]);
        }
        //right maximum
        for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){
            rmax[i] = max(rmax[i+1],height[i]);
        }
        //answer
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            ans+=min(lmax[i],rmax[i]) - height[i];
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

